io.proximax.dfms.cid.multihash

Class Multihash

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.proximax.dfms.cid.multihash.Multihash

  • public class Multihash
extends java.lang.Object
    Self-described hash. First 2 bytes represent type of the hashing function used ( MultihashType ) and length of the hashed data in bytes
    See Also:
    Multihash specification

    • Constructor Detail

      • Multihash

        public Multihash(MultihashType type,
                 byte[] hash)

        create new Multihash instance specifying type and hash bytes.

        NOTICE that hash byte array is internally used and even though this object is expected to be immutable it can be changed if the array is changed externally

        Parameters:
        type - type of the hashing algorithm
        hash - byte array representing the hash data

      • create

        public static Multihash create(byte[] multihashBytes)
        create new multihash instance from serialized bytes of another multihash instance. This assumes first byte is hash type index and second byte is length
        Parameters:

        Returns:
        multihash instance based on parameter
